@node Main "Labyx - Documentation"

                              'Labyx' V1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Labyx' is a Workbench @{"game" link play} where the goal is to find the exit in
the 59 by 59 spaces labyrinth, in the least amount of moves possible.
You can play it as any typical maze game...

  ...On the other hand, you can also play the game by rotating,
clockwise by 90 degres, the 8 tiles or empty spaces that surround
your position. This can make your task easier in order to find the
exit. However, if there are "riveted" tiles in those 8 surrounding
tiles, the tiles and empty spaces will not rotate.

  To complicate matters more, only a small portion (a 5 by 5 tile
area) of the labyrinth is shown.

  Have fun!

