@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Labyx" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  Your position is indicated by the smiling face icon in the center
of the display. To play, click on a space in the general direction
you want to move. If the move is possible (no walls blocking in the
choosen direction) the display is then updated at the new position.

  If you click on your position, and there are no "riveted" tiles
(tiles that have two small dots on them) in the 8 tiles and empty
spaces that surrond that position, those tiles and empty spaces
will rotate by 90 degres in a clockwise manner. This can help you
move more easily towards a location that would have taken many
moves to get to otherwise...

  The exit is marked by an "E" (or "Exit") and is always located in
a dead end somewhere on the edge of the gameboard. If you get on
that tile, the game ends and displays how many moves it took to get
there, then Labyx creates a new maze to explore...

  The game can be played by using the cursor keys. To pivot the 8
surrounding tiles and empty spaces, press on the space bar.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button (or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  Have fun!

@endnode

